The paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves maximizing a variational information bound, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves learning domain-invariant representations, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of reference images, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of randomly sampled codes, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
